.TH "kthread_queue_delayed_work" 9 "kthread_queue_delayed_work" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kthread_queue_delayed_work \- queue the associated kthread work after a delay.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" kthread_queue_delayed_work
.BI "(struct kthread_worker *worker "  ","
.BI "struct kthread_delayed_work *dwork "  ","
.BI "unsigned long delay "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "worker" 12
target kthread_worker
.IP "dwork" 12
kthread_delayed_work to queue
.IP "delay" 12
number of jiffies to wait before queuing
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the work has not been pending it starts a timer that will queue
the work after the given \fIdelay\fP. If \fIdelay\fP is zero, it queues the
work immediately.
.SH "RETURN"
false if the \fIwork\fP has already been pending. It means that
either the timer was running or the work was queued. It returns true
otherwise.
